description.narrative: Nearly 1,300 children in need of care and protection were handled by UNICEF-supported government social welfare services in five countries (Fiji, Kiribati, Nauru, Solomon Islands and Vanuatu). In addition, 510 child victims of abuse in Samoa and 43 children with disabilities in Vanuatu were handled through UNICEF support to local NGOs. Forty-nine government social welfare officers from three PICTs (Kiribati, Nauru and Solomon Islands) participated in the first ever practical skill-based training on child protection and social work with children in need of care and protection and their families in the Pacific, which participants found very helpful. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
